DB : user password : mysql : root/harshal

1) Spring JPA - java persistent object.
2) Spring jPA with mysql
3) spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/blog?useSSL=false
	- here adding "?useSSL=false" will disable use of SSL
4) spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create
   spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/blog?useSSL=false
   spring.datasource.username=root
   spring.datasource.password=harshal	
   
   using only this 4 line , spring application will be able to connect with database
5)   spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create ( none, update, create, or create-drop) 
	- create will create a db every time and and update will update db as per entity class